.TH "inet_pton_with_scope" 9 "inet_pton_with_scope" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
inet_pton_with_scope \- convert an IPv4/IPv6 and port to socket address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" inet_pton_with_scope
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "__kernel_sa_family_t af "  ","
.BI "const char *src "  ","
.BI "const char *port "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr_storage *addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
net namespace (used for scope handling)
.IP "af" 12
address family, AF_INET, AF_INET6 or AF_UNSPEC for either
.IP "src" 12
the start of the address string
.IP "port" 12
the start of the port string (or NULL for none)
.IP "addr" 12
output socket address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return zero on success, return errno when any error occurs.
